main event: Two white, round lights were observed in the sky near Lincoln Air Force Base, Nebraska on July 25, 1965.
interesting points: The first light flashed or dimmed out 6-7 times during its traverse across the sky, then dimmed out completely.
The second light was not as bright as the first.
The lights were moving 3-4 times faster than normal aircraft.
An 'echo' satellite was also observed passing by around the same time as the UFO sightings.
The observation was considered most likely to be a tumbling section of a spent missile in orbit reflecting sunlight.
witnesses: Colonel Frank W. *****, Lt Colonel *****, Mrs. *****, and Mrs. *****
